%description
Automatically type-check SQL statements at compile time. Uses Template Haskell
and the raw PostgreSQL protocol to describe SQL statements at compile time and
provide appropriate type marshalling for both parameters and results.
Allows not only syntax verification of your SQL but also full type safety
between your SQL and Haskell. Supports many built-in PostgreSQL types already,
including arrays and ranges, and can be easily extended in user code to support
any other types.

Also includes an optional HDBC backend that, since it uses the raw PostgreSQL
protocol, may be more efficient than the normal libpq backend in some cases
(though provides no more type safety than HDBC-postgresql when used without
templates).

Originally based on Chris Forno's templatepg library.


